The paper deals with network covert channels, which are a security concern in computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of patterns and pattern variations in covert channels, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also deals with network protocols, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses countermeasures against covert channels, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
